Sentencas: Reduced La0.4Sr0.6Co0.2Fe0.7NNb0.1O3-delta (LSCFN) with anchored nanoscale Co-Fe alloy is evaluated as the protective catalyst layer for ethanol-fueled solid oxide fuel cells (SOFCs) in this study.
Titulo: Direct power generation from ethanol by solid oxide fuel cells with an integrated catalyst layer

Sentencas: The coking resistance and overall performance of both cells with and without the catalyst layer are systematically studied in ethanol and H-2 fuels.
Titulo: Direct power generation from ethanol by solid oxide fuel cells with an integrated catalyst layer

Sentencas: Both cells with and without the catalyst layer fueled in H-2 fuel exhibit equivalent electrochemical performance, and the peak power density is 1065 and 1098 mW.cm(-2 )at 800 degrees C, respectively.
Titulo: Direct power generation from ethanol by solid oxide fuel cells with an integrated catalyst layer

Sentencas: When compared with the conventional cell in ethanol fuel, the cell cracking caused by thermal-mechanical stress can be avoided in the new cell design with an integrated catalyst layer.
Titulo: Direct power generation from ethanol by solid oxide fuel cells with an integrated catalyst layer

Sentencas: Also, it exhibits a considerable peak power density of 469 mW.cm(-2) and demonstrates good coking resistance, and is stable during the 76 h test in ethanol at 800 degrees C.
Titulo: Direct power generation from ethanol by solid oxide fuel cells with an integrated catalyst layer

Sentencas: This study shows that the addition of the LSCFN catalyst layer can protect Ni-YSZ from the uneven distributed thermal-mechanical stress and severe coking in ethanol fuel.
Titulo: Direct power generation from ethanol by solid oxide fuel cells with an integrated catalyst layer
